<TITLE> 24 players picked for national cricket academy </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, June 1 (bdnews24.com) - The Bangladesh Cricket Board on Monday picked 24 cricketers for the GP-BCB National Cricket Academy for the session of 2009-2010. The selected players have been requested to report to academy head coach Sri Lankan Ruwan Kalpage and project operation officer M Shahidul Islam on June 5 at Academy House in Mirpur. They are M Mithun, Rony Talukder, Habibur Rahman, Nadimuddin Mintu, Mayshequr Rahman, Nasir Hossain, Shuvagoto Hom, Nizamuddin Ripon, Marshal Ayub, Forhad Hossain, Tanvir Haider, Muktar Ali, Suvashish Roy, Emon Ahmed, Shafiul Islam, Kamrul Islam, M Azim, Robiul Islam, Ariful Hoque, Syed Golam Kibria, Saqlain Sajib, M Shakil, Sanjamul Islam, Hamidul Islam The team management for GP-BCB National Cricket Academy are Ruwan Kalpage (Academy head coach), Sarwar Imran (head pace bowling coach), Bayjedul Islam (physio / fitness trainer) and Mohammad Salauddin (computer analyst). bd
